I requested this file
weeks ago,
and it took this long.

12:35.480 --> 12:38.608
Look. It's nothing.
All right?

12:39.250 --> 12:40.888
See?
Thank you.

12:40.920 --> 12:43.354
We good?
I'll call in
the surveillance op.

12:43.390 --> 12:45.779
**

12:48.130 --> 12:50.496
Megan Marie.
She's our eldest.

12:50.530 --> 12:54.193
And she got her acceptance
letter last week in the mail.

12:54.240 --> 12:55.935
And... (LAUGHS)

12:55.970 --> 12:58.336
You've never seen
a kid smile so big.

12:58.370 --> 13:00.838
(CHUCKLES) No matter
how bad things are,

13:00.880 --> 13:03.269
my world just lights up
when that kid's happy.

13:03.310 --> 13:05.676
(CHUCKLES)

13:05.710 --> 13:07.917
Wsumm

13:07.950 --> 13:09.770
It's Middlebury College.

13:12.820 --> 13:18.429
And now she can't go
because, um, I lost her
tuition money at the track.

13:19.930 --> 13:21.795
And, um...

13:21.830 --> 13:23.627
And I haven't told her yet.
I mean, how can I tell her?

13:23.670 --> 13:25.888
I'm not gonna break her heart.

13:25.930 --> 13:29.263
(CRYING) Let her know
what kind of man
her father really is.

13:30.110 --> 13:32.066
(INHALES SHARPLY)

13:32.110 --> 13:34.772
I would do anything
to make this right.

13:34.810 --> 13:37.404
**

13:37.450 --> 13:38.974
(SIGHS)

13:39.010 --> 13:41.342
(OWL HOOTING)

13:41.380 --> 13:43.439
(ENGINE IDLING)

13:44.190 --> 13:47.910
**

13:47.960 --> 13:51.623
* Here, take my heart

13:51.660 --> 13:54.493
* On a silver platter *

13:54.530 --> 13:55.827
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

13:55.860 --> 13:57.225
Really, Ned?

13:57.270 --> 13:59.261
This doesn't look like
a solution to me.

13:59.300 --> 14:01.996
Most insurance policies
don't even cover suicides.

14:02.040 --> 14:03.507
Who the hell are you?
How did you get in here?

14:03.540 --> 14:06.668
You want to go
to Megan Marie's college
celebration, don't ya,

14:06.710 --> 14:08.109
like a good father
should?

14:08.140 --> 14:09.869
How... How did you
know about that?

14:09.910 --> 14:12.140
I know lots of things.

14:12.180 --> 14:14.512
I know you gambled away
Megan's tuition.

14:14.550 --> 14:16.882
And I know about the bookies
and the dodgy loans,

14:16.920 --> 14:18.615
not to mention

14:18.650 --> 14:21.118
the damn Lakers neglecting
to cover their spread.

14:21.160 --> 14:23.788
You're a debt collector.
Of sorts.

14:23.830 --> 14:25.457
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

14:25.490 --> 14:26.787
I got nothing left
to give.

14:26.830 --> 14:29.025
Oh, don't sell
yourself short.

14:29.060 --> 14:30.960
You've got you.

14:31.730 --> 14:33.368
But tell me,
do you have the courage

14:33.400 --> 14:34.731
to make one more bet?

14:36.140 --> 14:37.562
This time, on yourself?

14:47.250 --> 14:49.138
PUTNUM: So, who's
the next unfortunate?

14:49.180 --> 14:52.388
Martin Walcott.
Do you know him?

14:52.420 --> 14:54.479
Walcott?
No, I don't think so.
What'd he do?

14:54.520 --> 14:56.613
Skim off the top
while you were away?

14:56.660 --> 15:00.824
On the contrary.
He recorded record profits.

15:00.860 --> 15:02.225
So what's your beef?

15:02.260 --> 15:05.491
WALCO'I'I': Raymond!
It's been too long.

15:05.530 --> 15:07.236
Martin Walcott,
Smokey Putnam.

15:07.270 --> 15:08.999
PUTNUM:
Yeah, nice to meet you.

15:09.700 --> 15:11.031
I brought the book.

15:11.070 --> 15:14.403
I figured you'd want
to go over the numbers.

15:14.440 --> 15:16.408
Smokey used to run
with the circus.

15:16.440 --> 15:19.978
Handled logistics.
Trains in, trains out.

15:20.020 --> 15:23.012
I'm surprised the two of you
haven't crossed paths.

15:23.050 --> 15:24.745
I'm just a sideshow
for Martin.

15:24.790 --> 15:27.918
He's a senior VP
at a railroad

15:27.960 --> 15:31.418
that runs freight between
New Mexico and Illinois.

15:31.460 --> 15:34.429
That a fact?
Yeah, I'm surprised
we never hooked up.

15:34.460 --> 15:36.928
REDDINGTON: Let me ask you
something, Martin,

15:36.970 --> 15:39.268
and I want a simple
yes or no.

15:39.300 --> 15:41.165
(BOOK CLOSES)

15:41.200 --> 15:43.134
Did you turn me in
to the police?

15:43.170 --> 15:44.933
Red, what?

15:44.970 --> 15:49.009
No! Of course not.
Why would you
ever ask me that?

15:49.040 --> 15:51.349
Because that's
an awfully big number.

15:51.380 --> 15:55.271
And the only way you could've
hit it was if I was in prison.

15:56.250 --> 15:57.740
Ithought
you'd be pleased.

15:57.790 --> 16:00.850
Did you?
I don't think so.

16:00.890 --> 16:02.710
If you thought
I'd be pleased,

16:02.760 --> 16:05.388
the book would reflect
how you hit the number.

16:05.430 --> 16:07.057
But it doesn't do that,
does it?

16:08.000 --> 16:10.218
It's a big number
because you cut a deal

16:10.270 --> 16:13.797
with the Catela Cartel
to run methamphetamine.

16:15.300 --> 16:17.632
You used my network,

16:17.670 --> 16:22.471
my trucks, my drivers,
my warehouses.

16:24.080 --> 16:26.401
If you're not gonna be
in the drug business,

16:26.450 --> 16:28.418
somebody else will be.

16:28.450 --> 16:30.782
It's not like we're gonna
stop it from coming in, right?

16:30.820 --> 16:32.481
(CHUCKLES)

16:33.490 --> 16:37.119
I'm not in the _
methamphetamine busmess.

16:37.160 --> 16:39.287
It's a poison.

16:40.030 --> 16:41.827
You traded on my name.

16:43.600 --> 16:45.818
I'm a relatively
forgiving man.

16:45.870 --> 16:47.428
But that...

16:48.640 --> 16:49.959
That, I can't forgive.

16:50.000 --> 16:53.299
Red. Hold on, hold on.
I thought that you...

16:53.340 --> 16:54.876
What do you think?

16:54.910 --> 16:57.299
Me?
Yeah.

16:57.350 --> 17:01.138
What do you think
I should do with Martin?

17:01.180 --> 17:02.670
I'm curious.

17:05.620 --> 17:08.088
I don't know. I-I guess...
(CLEARS THROAT)

17:08.120 --> 17:10.350
On one hand,
he kind of betrayed you.

17:10.390 --> 17:13.029
I say "kind of" because
when you were in prison,

17:13.060 --> 17:16.393
maybe he was thinking,
in that situation,
he had some latitude.

17:18.470 --> 17:22.133
You said, "On the one hand."
Is there another?

17:22.170 --> 17:24.434
(ICE RA'I'I'LING)
Yeah. No, of course.

17:24.470 --> 17:26.233
I mean, look,
I never killed anyone.

17:26.270 --> 17:27.976
When it comes to people,
I'm vegan.

17:28.010 --> 17:29.568
(LAUGHS)

17:29.610 --> 17:31.407
So if it was up to me,

17:31.450 --> 17:33.008
and... And let's all
reflect on

17:33.050 --> 17:34.642
how awesome it is
that it's not,

17:34.680 --> 17:37.808
but if it was, I guess
I'd opt for firing him.

17:37.850 --> 17:39.488
Or fining him,
like you did
with Androssani.

17:39.520 --> 17:40.817
I mean, both these guys
are family guys.

17:40.860 --> 17:42.157
Androssani's got a wife.

17:42.190 --> 17:43.521
He's got a kid.
So, you know...

17:43.560 --> 17:45.448
Anyway, that's why you do
the strategic thinking

17:45.490 --> 17:46.752
and I stick to logistics.

17:47.830 --> 17:50.424
**

17:53.700 --> 17:56.134
(CUPS RA'I'I'LING)

17:56.170 --> 17:58.661
(ICE RA'I'I'LING)

17:58.710 --> 18:01.270
**

18:05.480 --> 18:08.643
G. Gordon Liddy
was an architect

18:08.680 --> 18:10.614
of the Watergate break-in.

18:11.820 --> 18:14.983
A strident true-believer
who trained himself

18:15.020 --> 18:18.979
to be_ unemotional about
d0ing terrible things.

18:19.030 --> 18:22.522
He'd literally
test himself by fire.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.198
(MATCH STRIKES)

18:24.230 --> 18:26.391
**

18:28.800 --> 18:32.167
Holding his hand
over a flame

18:32.210 --> 18:35.338
without flinching
as his flesh burned.

18:35.380 --> 18:37.439
People thought
it was a trick.

18:37.480 --> 18:40.005
He said the trick
is not minding.

18:40.050 --> 18:41.938
Ahh.
(INHALES SHARPLY)

18:41.980 --> 18:43.686
I mind.

18:43.720 --> 18:45.608
**

18:45.650 --> 18:47.049
(BLOWING)

18:47.090 --> 18:49.354
I mind.

18:49.390 --> 18:51.028
(BLOWING)

18:51.060 --> 18:53.654
**

19:05.070 --> 19:06.958
REDDINGTON: Mmm.

19:07.010 --> 19:08.602
**

19:11.310 --> 19:14.916
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

19:14.950 --> 19:18.886
You got no idea
how much I missed you, Tea.

19:18.920 --> 19:20.717
What's going on?

19:20.760 --> 19:22.455
HENRY: You gotta know,
everything I did,

19:22.490 --> 19:24.048
I did it for us.

19:24.090 --> 19:26.650
RESSLER: Keen,
you getting this?
Every word.

19:26.690 --> 19:29.796
LIZ: Tango Team, the minute
you get verbal confirmation,
move in.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.127
Assume he's armed.
WOMAN: Copy that.

19:31.170 --> 19:32.592
HENRY: I made us square.

19:32.630 --> 19:35.428
There's no more debt.
But how?

19:35.470 --> 19:37.734
We're gonna be able to
pay off all of our loans.

19:37.770 --> 19:40.330
And we... We can start over.
We'll go somewhere else.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.177
We'll go somewhere warm.
Keen, heads up.

19:42.210 --> 19:43.973
We got a White male
near the playground.

19:44.810 --> 19:46.368
You think his wife
tipped someone?

19:46.410 --> 19:48.469
RESSLER:
Or Morris brought a plus-one.
I'm gonna check it out.

19:48.520 --> 19:50.488
HENRY: I stopped
by the pawn shop.

19:50.520 --> 19:51.680
If you've done
something illegal,

19:51.720 --> 19:53.142
you need to tell me,
please.

19:53.190 --> 19:54.817
I have something for ya.

19:56.960 --> 19:58.951
**

19:58.990 --> 20:00.298
RESSLER: We've got a gun.

20:00.330 --> 20:01.797
FBI! Stop!

20:01.830 --> 20:03.092
FBI! Hands!

20:03.130 --> 20:05.018
(GUNSHOTS, TERESA SCREAMS)

20:05.070 --> 20:07.265
Put it down, put it down!
Don't move!

20:07.300 --> 20:09.359
LIZ: Henry Morris,
you're under arrest

20:09.400 --> 20:11.038
for the murder
of Betsy Nagel.

20:12.040 --> 20:13.473
I'm so sorry.

20:13.510 --> 20:15.671
(CRYING) Henry,
What have you done?

20:17.550 --> 20:19.609
RESSLER:
I went over the manifest,
and I think I found something.

20:19.650 --> 20:21.015
WARD: I'm glad
to hear it, Don,

20:21.050 --> 20:22.540
but I'm in the middle
of a big briefing here.

20:22.580 --> 20:24.639
Dead or alive,
everyone's accounted for.

20:24.690 --> 20:26.681
Except one.
Then you need me because?

20:26.720 --> 20:28.551
Because that one person
doesn't exist

20:28.590 --> 20:30.182
before buying a ticket
for that ferry.

20:30.220 --> 20:31.949
Everything about her,

20:31.990 --> 20:34.788
credit rating,
social security,
mortgage payments,

20:34.830 --> 20:37.958
it exists only after
she bought that ticket,
not before.

20:38.000 --> 20:40.389
Seriously, I am in a room
full of people

20:40.440 --> 20:42.032
waiting on me to give
a threat assessment.

20:42.070 --> 20:44.436
It's important, M].
I need your help.

20:44.470 --> 20:45.835
It's also off-book,

20:45.870 --> 20:47.508
so I'm gonna have to
farm out the legwork.

20:47.540 --> 20:50.407
IfI send you what I have,
can you do the due diligence
for me?

20:50.450 --> 20:55.342
It's gonna cost me,
but for you,
Crimea can wait.

20:55.380 --> 20:57.143
I owe you, pal. Thanks.
(BEEP)

20:57.180 --> 20:59.387
(DOOR SLIDING)

20:59.420 --> 21:01.809
**

21:01.860 --> 21:04.249
NED: This bandage
isn't enough.

21:04.290 --> 21:05.928
I-I really need
to go to a hospital.

21:05.960 --> 21:07.928
Not until you answer
my question.

21:07.960 --> 21:09.996
Look, I don't know
how to find her.

21:10.030 --> 21:12.567
Because she came to you.
Yes! At the house.

21:12.600 --> 21:14.534
I mean, it was like
she was studying me.

21:14.570 --> 21:16.060
She... She had
all kinds of information.

21:16.100 --> 21:17.408
LIZ: What kind
of information?

21:17.440 --> 21:19.328
HENRY: Everything...
How many months'
rent I owed,

21:19.370 --> 21:21.577
how much I lost that night
in Atlantic City.

21:21.610 --> 21:22.872
NED: She knew
my favorite teams.

21:22.910 --> 21:24.400
She knew how much I owed.

21:24.450 --> 21:26.839
She said that she could make
all that debt go away.

21:26.880 --> 21:29.110
LIZ: How?
What exactly did she say?

21:29.150 --> 21:33.917
That, uh, my gambling
had become a cancer
on the people I love.

21:33.960 --> 21:36.485
She said that I needed
to start over.

21:36.520 --> 21:38.522
What does that mean?
Start over how?

21:38.560 --> 21:40.084
_ HENRY:
By domg her a favor.

21:40.130 --> 21:43.463
She asked me to...
Take care of someone for her.

21:43.500 --> 21:45.468
And by "taking care of"
someone,

21:45.500 --> 21:47.468
you mean drowning Betsy Nagel
in her bathtub?

21:47.500 --> 21:49.639
Well, it was supposed to
look like something else,

21:49.670 --> 21:51.228
like a robbery.

21:51.270 --> 21:54.068
A gunshot in broad daylight
wasn't exactly subtle, Ned.

21:54.110 --> 21:55.805
I'm guessing she didn't
sign off on that.

21:55.840 --> 21:58.104
HENRY: Look,
I may never get out
of jail for what I've done,

21:58.150 --> 21:59.902
but I did it
to help my family.

21:59.950 --> 22:02.714
And if I was
smart enough,

22:02.750 --> 22:04.547
I would've got away
With it, too.

22:04.590 --> 22:07.753
LIZ: Henry, you were never
gonna get away with it.

22:07.790 --> 22:09.917
Because you were always
gonna be her next victim.

22:11.660 --> 22:13.321
What do you mean,
"her next victim"?

22:13.360 --> 22:15.328
It's gamblers
killing gamblers.

22:15.360 --> 22:17.089
Lady Luck
identifies her target,

22:17.130 --> 22:19.018
someone Who has a significant
amount of debt,

22:19.070 --> 22:21.664
to be her hitman,
and then she offers to
pay off that debt

22:21.700 --> 22:23.463
in exchange
for the killing.

22:23.510 --> 22:26.331
But What the killer
doesn't know is that
he's the next victim.

22:26.370 --> 22:27.928
Like Betsy Nagel?

22:27.980 --> 22:30.278
Turns out, she'd been bleeding
her sister dry for years

22:30.310 --> 22:31.800
to pay off
her gambling debt.

22:31.850 --> 22:33.670
I spoke to the sister,
and she said that Betsy

22:33.720 --> 22:35.676
showed up last month,
paid her back,

22:35.720 --> 22:38.644
paid her mortgage,
and a half-dozen
maxed-out credit cards.

22:38.690 --> 22:41.011
Using money she'd gotten
for killing a gambler.

22:41.060 --> 22:42.914
And Miss Nagel
is not alone.

22:42.960 --> 22:45.326
I looked into
suspicious deaths
of known gamblers

22:45.360 --> 22:49.228
Who squared debts
shortly before dying,
and get this...

22:49.730 --> 22:51.266
Janice Deavers,

22:51.300 --> 22:54.133
a gunshot wound to the chest
off the Vegas Strip.

22:54.170 --> 22:58.209
Jeff Warner, stabbed to death
in the parking lot
of a casino in Connecticut.

22:58.240 --> 22:59.468
And there are more.

22:59.510 --> 23:02.809
So Lady Luck's
outsourcing her kills.

23:02.840 --> 23:04.808
But Why spend all this money
on bribing gamblers?

23:04.850 --> 23:06.044
Why not kill them herself?

23:06.080 --> 23:08.514
Where's the bribe money
coming from to begin With?

23:08.550 --> 23:11.519
I don't know, but her
cash supply seems endless.

23:11.550 --> 23:14.883
Which means she won't stop.
COOPER: Ned Green.
Lean on him.

23:14.920 --> 23:17.423
Find out how he contacts this
woman after the hit's done.

23:17.460 --> 23:18.620
One way or the other,

23:18.660 --> 23:20.719
Green's gonna put us
in touch with Lady Luck.

23:23.330 --> 23:24.888
This is my final offer,

23:24.930 --> 23:26.795
and I think you'll
want to accept it.

23:26.830 --> 23:28.559
RStms
or it's nothing.

23:28.600 --> 23:30.966
You finish all your peas,

23:31.010 --> 23:34.229
and I'll let you watch
PJ Masks before your nap.

23:34.280 --> 23:35.907
Do we have a deal?

23:39.710 --> 23:41.519
(CHUCKLING)
Smart move, mister.

23:41.550 --> 23:43.882
(DOOR OPENS, KEYS JINGLING)

23:44.850 --> 23:48.388
Hey, everyone.
Sorry I'm late.

23:48.420 --> 23:51.025
Mmm.
What are we up to?

23:51.060 --> 23:52.823
_ AGATHE_: _
Culinary negotiations.

23:52.860 --> 23:57.126
Ahh. Thanks, Mom.
I'd be lost without you.

23:57.160 --> 24:00.698
Picked up a shift
from Sherry on Tuesday.

24:00.740 --> 24:03.163
Any chance you might be free
to watch Joey?

24:03.200 --> 24:04.701
It shouldn't be a problem.

24:04.740 --> 24:06.765
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

24:06.810 --> 24:08.698
Oh, who the heck
is this?

24:11.180 --> 24:13.910
Oh, I don't know no one
from 2-1-6.

24:13.950 --> 24:16.111
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

24:16.150 --> 24:17.708
(BEEP)

24:17.750 --> 24:19.047
Is it done?

24:19.090 --> 24:20.443
NED: We hit a snag.

24:20.490 --> 24:21.752
AGATHE: What snag?

24:21.790 --> 24:23.087
Not over the phone.
C-Can we meet?

24:25.990 --> 24:27.423
There's a spot on Route 9.

24:27.460 --> 24:29.519
Orangetown Diner.
Meet me at 4:00.

24:29.560 --> 24:31.198
If you're late,
the deal's off.

24:31.230 --> 24:34.165
And you can go back to your
garage and start the engine.

24:37.910 --> 24:39.764
(GAME SHOW PLAYING
ON TELEVISION)

24:39.810 --> 24:42.278
I don't know, Lou.

24:42.310 --> 24:44.608
He called out of nowhere,
sounded worried.

24:44.650 --> 24:47.619
This one may not be
up to the task.

24:47.650 --> 24:48.912
I know What you're thinking.

24:48.950 --> 24:52.442
We've been dealt
far worse hands before,
and we're still here.

24:52.490 --> 24:55.254
I'll be back for dinner.
Do you want anything special?

24:55.290 --> 24:57.758
(CHUCKLES)
Don't answer that.

24:57.790 --> 24:59.929
I'll think of something.

24:59.960 --> 25:03.259
MAN ON TV:
That's it. You have $300...

25:03.300 --> 25:05.825
**

25:08.000 --> 25:10.161
Why pick
this place to meet?

25:10.200 --> 25:12.839
I don't know. I don't like
it, either. It's too public.

25:12.870 --> 25:14.633
NED: I told you.
She'll be here.

25:14.680 --> 25:17.979
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
Hello?

25:18.010 --> 25:20.843
AGATHE: Oh, Ned,
I expected
better from you.

25:20.880 --> 25:21.972
NED: What are you
talking about?

25:22.020 --> 25:23.715
I-I'm here exactly
Where you told me to be.

25:23.750 --> 25:26.810
Unlike you, I know how
to hedge my bets, Ned.

25:26.850 --> 25:28.852
That's got to be her.

25:28.890 --> 25:30.755
My husband took me
to that diner

25:30.790 --> 25:33.657
to watch Sunday football
for 15 years.

25:33.700 --> 25:35.588
I know the regulars.

25:35.630 --> 25:38.519
I knew Ben Sherman, who always
comes in for his 4:00 coffee.

25:38.570 --> 25:40.322
Ben's not there.

25:40.370 --> 25:41.689
I know Dale and Toddy,

25:41.740 --> 25:44.504
Who work splits on Fridays,
and they're not there.

25:44.540 --> 25:46.633
She's watching. You got eyes?
She's not in here.

25:46.670 --> 25:49.377
Heck, Ned, we got
a Whole lot of new faces,

25:49.410 --> 25:51.844
enough to make me think you've
been talking to the police.

25:53.050 --> 25:55.177
You know the problem
With gamblers, Ned?

25:55.220 --> 25:57.017
