I'll do Whatever you ask.

28:52.590 --> 28:54.558
Have you ever had
a flying dream?

28:55.560 --> 28:56.652
What?

28:56.700 --> 29:00.158
A dream in which you suddenly
have the power of flight.

29:02.240 --> 29:06.506
Unburdened by the weight
of apprehension and doubt,

29:06.540 --> 29:10.203
you suddenly find
you can fly.

29:10.240 --> 29:13.243
It's a dream of
freedom and bliss.

29:17.750 --> 29:20.344
The opposite
of a falling dream,

29:20.390 --> 29:23.928
Which, of course, is a dream
of fear and anxiety, panic.

29:25.760 --> 29:27.580
**

29:30.060 --> 29:31.789
Flying is life.

29:37.770 --> 29:39.567
Falling is death.

29:39.610 --> 29:42.033
**

29:58.290 --> 30:01.259
Mommy says by the time
your program's done,
she'll be here.

30:01.300 --> 30:03.723
That's no nuts...

30:03.760 --> 30:05.967
I'm going on a trip.

30:06.000 --> 30:08.639
While I'm gone, I want you
to be good for your ma.

30:08.670 --> 30:12.629
She's gonna have a lot to do
and nobody to help her do it.

30:12.670 --> 30:13.807
Huh?

30:13.840 --> 30:18.800
When you get bigger,
people are gonna
say things about me.

30:18.850 --> 30:21.444
Not-so-nice things.

30:21.480 --> 30:23.175
But I want you to know,

30:23.220 --> 30:27.418
What I did,
I did as a kindness.

30:27.450 --> 30:28.951
Can you remember that?

30:30.590 --> 30:32.649
**

30:35.530 --> 30:39.626
(CRYING) I love my
little monster. So much.

30:40.170 --> 30:41.990
I love you, too, Grammy.

30:47.140 --> 30:49.176
**

